## Commands

```bash
bunx tsc --noEmit            # type-check (MUST pass before done)
bun test                     # unit tests
<% if (Type === 'api') { -%>
SERVICE_BACKEND=stub bun run src/index.ts   # canned responses, no DB/redis
SERVICE_BACKEND=real bun run src/index.ts   # full stack
<% } else { -%>
bun run src/index.ts         # connect to <%= Broker %>
<% } -%>
<% if (Database !== 'none') { -%>
SERVICE_BACKEND=real bun run src/cmd/seed.ts   # seed 25 rows
bunx drizzle-kit generate    # migration from src/db/schema
<% } -%>
```

After editing any `.ts`, run `mcp__ts-lsp__ts_diagnose` then `bunx tsc --noEmit`. Don't report done until both are clean.

## Layout & the dependency rule

```
<% if (Type === 'publisher') { -%>
src/domain/<%= EntityLower %>.ts                  business types (camelCase)
config/config.ts                      env-driven config
src/adapter/outbound/publisher/       <%= Entity %> event publisher (wraps pubsub.Publisher)
src/index.ts                          composition root — creates the <%= Broker %> publisher
<% } else { -%>
src/domain/      business types (camelCase)         ← depends on nothing
src/port/        interfaces (Repository, Service)    ← the contracts
src/service/     use-cases                           ← imports port/ ONLY (never an adapter)
src/apperr/      error-code registry
src/adapter/inbound/<%= Type === 'api' ? 'http/        thin Elysia controller + TypeBox DTO' : 'subscriber/   message handler (decode → service)' %>
<% if (Database !== 'none') { -%>
src/adapter/outbound/repository/  Drizzle repo (BaseRepo/CachedRepo)
<% } -%>
src/index.ts     composition root — wires everything; the ONLY place that touches concrete adapters
<% } -%>
```

<% if (Type === 'publisher') { -%>
**DIP (MUST):** the publisher adapter depends on the `Publisher` port from `@labspangaea/ts-lib/pubsub` —
swap the broker without touching call sites. Wiring happens only in `src/index.ts`.
<% } else { -%>
**DIP (MUST):** `service/` and the inbound adapter depend on `port/` interfaces, never on a
concrete repository/cache/broker. Wiring happens only in `src/index.ts`.
<% } -%>

**OCP (SHOULD):** add behavior by adding files (a new service method, a new entity via the
scaffolder), not by editing existing switch/factory blocks.

## Conventions (load-bearing)

<% if (Type !== 'publisher') { -%>
- **Errors:** `throw new ApiError(Err<%= Entity %>...)` — never build `{status:false,...}` JSON by hand.
  The server plugin's `onError` renders the envelope (`ApiError`→its status, validation→422,
  not-found→404, invalid cursor→400, else→500). Define codes in `src/apperr/<%= EntityLower %>.ts`.
<% } -%>
<% if (Type === 'api') { -%>
- **Wire vs domain:** the domain is camelCase; the HTTP wire is snake_case. Map ONLY in the DTO
  (`bodyToInput` / `toResponse`) — never serialize the domain object straight to the response.
- **Validation:** declare a TypeBox `body:` schema on the route. It drives both runtime validation
  AND the OpenAPI spec. No second validator.
<% } else { -%>
- **Wire vs domain:** the domain is camelCase; the broker payload is snake_case JSON. Map at the
  <%= Type === 'consumer' ? 'subscriber (decode → service input)' : 'publisher (to' + Entity + 'Event)' %> boundary.
<% } -%>
<% if (Database !== 'none') { -%>
- **Timestamps:** `created_at`/`updated_at` are `bigint` epoch-ms columns. The driver returns
  bigint as a **string**, so the repository coerces `new Date(Number(col))` — a bare
  `new Date(col)` yields `Invalid Date`. Domain Dates serialize to ISO on the wire.
- **Updates:** pass an explicit column list to `repo.update` so `id`/`created_at` are never clobbered.
<% } -%>
- **Durations are milliseconds** everywhere (TTLs, timeouts).
- **Logging:** `import { fromContext } from '@labspangaea/ts-lib/logger'; fromContext().info(...)` inside
  methods — never a struct/field logger. AsyncLocalStorage carries the request-bound logger
  (request_id/trace_id) automatically. No hardcoded timeouts in `index.ts` — read `cfg.*`.
<% if (Type === 'api') { -%>
- **Stub:** `src/service/stub/<%= EntityLower %>.ts` is stateless with deterministic ids
  (`<%= EntityLower %>-stub-<i>`). Keep create/update/delete as no-ops — it must NOT pretend to persist.
  It is excluded from the production build via `bun build` tree-shaking.
<% } else if (Type === 'consumer') { -%>
- **Handler lifecycle:** a handler that resolves ACKs, a throw NACKs/requeues. Don't tie the handler
  to a shutdown signal — in-flight work runs to completion (the `context.WithoutCancel` analogue).
<% } -%>

## Adding to this service

- New entity → `/elysia-scaffolder:create-elysia-repository` (then service, then handler).
- New endpoint on <%= Entity %> → edit `src/adapter/inbound/http/<%= EntityLower %>.ts` + its DTO.
- Library API reference: `@labspangaea/ts-lib` (see the plugin's `references/codebase.md`).
